benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/payments - Trigger a payment using the account external key

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC06, @TC22, @TC23, @TC25, @TC26, @TC27, @TC30 cover successful creation with required and optional parameters.

Invalid Payload: @TC09 covers malformed request body; @TC11 covers invalid paymentMethodId; @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC16, @TC17, @TC18, @TC20, @TC21, @TC24, @TC28, @TC29 cover various error scenarios including declined, aborted, timeout, unauthorized, and dependency failures.
Missing Required Parameters: @TC08 covers missing externalKey; @TC10 covers missing header X-Killbill-CreatedBy.

Edge Cases & Boundary Tests: @TC22, @TC23, @TC21, @TC20, @TC26, @TC27, @TC22, @TC23, @TC21, @TC20, @TC26, @TC27, @TC22, @TC23, @TC21, @TC20, @TC26, @TC27 cover boundary and minimal/maximal input scenarios.
Security & Malicious Payloads: @TC18 tests malicious payload handling.
Regression & Compatibility: @TC25, @TC26 ensure backward compatibility and regression fixes.
Performance & Load: @TC27, @TC28, @TC29 cover response time, load, and resource utilization under different conditions.
Error Handling & Gateway Failures: @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC16, @TC17, @TC24 cover various failure modes and error responses.
Special Cases: @TC06 covers account with no default payment method but with paymentMethodId; @TC07, @TC20, @TC24 cover non-existent accounts and empty database scenarios.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized or invalid tokens beyond @TC17.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Duplicate Submission: No tests explicitly check idempotency or handling of duplicate requests.
Soft Deletes & Concurrency: No tests for soft delete behavior or race conditions on resource updates.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling to verify correct behavior with large datasets.
Include explicit authorization tests with invalid or missing tokens to ensure security measures.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system robustness under load.
Test caching headers and behaviors, such as ETag validation and cache control directives.
Create scenarios for duplicate submissions to verify idempotency and conflict handling.
Add concurrency tests for race conditions and soft delete behaviors.
